The Caretaker Extra-Ordinary Convention Planning Committee of the All Progressives Congress will today (Friday) roll out the time-table for its congresses nationwide. It was gathered that the roll out which was scheduled for next week, was brought forward following remarks made by the President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), in an interview with Arise Television on Thursday. The President had said the panel was given till the end of June to submit its report. It was gathered that the caretaker committee held an emergency meeting to deliberate on the way forward. A time-table which was released, but later withdrawn indicated that ward congresses would begin on July 10th, while local government congresses would follow on August 6, 2021. State congresses were scheduled for September 3 and zonal congresses for 30th September, 2021. Secretary to the Committee, Senator John James Akpanduoehehe, who spoke to reporters after the meeting of the caretaker committee said, “The organising Secretary will make the timetable available to you.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com